stylometry: The general trade off that you face when managing inventory is the trade off between ordering and carrying costs. This trade off is that you need to know the correct amount to order so that it will match the rates of demand and so that you won't have too much inventory laying around making carrying costs high. You want to minimze carrying costs while still having enough on hand to make all the sales you might incure. You also need to minimize your ordering costs though without ordering too little so that you run out of inventory if the demand rises causing you to lose sales.
